nd risks. Moreover, we have to analyse the 'invention' of conservation as a moral enterprise. That is why environmental history needs a long durée's perspective to understand the evolution of the European Common.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 4aEuropäische Union. 4aUmwelt. 4aUmweltpolitik. 4aÖkonomie.  aEconomy.  aEnvironment.  aEnvironmental policy.  aEuropean Union.1 aAschwanden, Romed, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBont, Raf de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuck, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoates, Peter A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEckert, Astrid M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrift, Liesbeth van de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGroß, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHasenöhrl, Ute, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHölzl, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaijser, Arne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirchhof, Astrid Mignon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKupper, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKupper, Patrick, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLaakkonen, Simo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeurs, Wim van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Jan-Henrik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOosthoek, K. Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRäsänen, Tuomas